==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trichomanes
<hw>Tri*chom"a*nes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a kind of
plant, from Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any fern of the genus
<gen>Trichomanes</gen>. The fronds are very delicate and often
translucent, and the sporangia are borne on threadlike receptacles
rising from the middle of cup-shaped marginal involucres. Several
species are common in conservatories; two are native in the United
States.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trichomatose</ent>⟦br⟧
